mkdir my-angular-app

cd my-angular-app

npm i @angular/cli

ng new my-angular-app --directory ./

ng serve


git remote add origin https://github.com/piratheesht/my-angular-app.git

git remote -v

git push -u origin master //refresh and see the content you must create repository in the same name


change angular.json outputpath to docs/

ng build --prod --baseHref="https://piratheesht.github.io/my-angular-app/"

git add .

git commit -m "generated deploy
git push -u origin master

Configure Your GitHub Repository for Publishing on GitHub Pages
Once the docs folder is pushed into your GitHub repository, you need to open the repository settings and go to the GitHub Pages section and select “master branch/docs folder” from the source dropdown. And that's it!

